article.description: Kelsey Plum scored 26 points, hitting 11 of 12 from the free-throw line, to lead Washington past Utah 73-60 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Washington women roll past Utah 73-60
article.story:
SEATTLE --  Kelsey Plum scored 26 points, hitting 11 of 12 from the free-throw line, to lead Washington past Utah 73-60 on Thursday night.

Talia Walton added 20 points and Chantel Osahor had 18 to go with 14 rebounds for Washington (19-9, 10-7 Pac-12). Plum reached 750 points for the season, breaking her own single-season school record of 746 on a pair of three throws in the fourth quarter.

The Huskies were outrebounded 42-39 but sank 17 of 19 from the line compared to Utah's 7 for 8.

Trailing 17-9 in the first quarter, Washington overtook Utah during a 13-0 run that made it 22-17 and led the rest of the way. Walton scored eight points in the go-ahead run.

Emily Potter paced Utah (15-13, 7-10) with 17 points and 11 rebounds. Katie Kuklok added 15 points, Paige Crozon had 11 and Danielle Rodriguez 10.
